result.execSummary:
The defendant Brenda L Murphy was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Brenda L Murphy in court with attorney Matt Last.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to counts 2 and 3.  Court finds the defendant guilty of counts 2 and 3.  Count #1 is dismissed and read in.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Last makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  

The Court Orders the Following: Count #2
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
6 months Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  (Credit - 0 days).  May be served in Sheboygan County if revoked, but only with Huber.  Consecutive to count #3 if revoked.  

Term of Probation: 1 Year, may be in Sheboygan County.  
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
No contact with Pick N Save, Walmart, or co-defendant Jessica S.  
Restitution: Complete Total = $1531.95 to be paid joint and several with co-defendant.  BAIL TO BE APPLIED FROM CASE # 15CM1001.  
Restitution Broken Down:  $936.33 to be paid to Roundys as a condition of probation.  $341.82 to be paid to Roundys from Read In case # 15CM1011, as a condition of probation.  $253.80 to be paid to Walmart from Read in Case # 15CM1001 as a condition of probation.  
COSTS:  $253.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA previously done, waived by court.  

The Court orders the following:  Count #3.  
Imposed sentence of:
90 days jail, first 10 days to be served in Waukesha County Jail without huber release.  Remainder of sentence may be served in Sheboygan County with Huber standard release conditions.  (credit 5 days).  Sentence commences immediately, taken into custody.  
COSTS:  $243.00 to be paid as a condition of her probation.
